subSubSection.paragraph:
This species is similar to 
Rhyncaphytoptus guanegounis
Song, Xue & Hong, 2007b, but can be differentiated from the latter by median, admedian and submedian lines present on prodorsal shield (prodorsal shield smooth in 
Rhyncaphytoptus guanegounis
), prodorsal shield with wide and broad frontal lobe (prodorsal shield with long and broad frontal lobe in 
Rhyncaphytoptus guanegounis
), opisthosomal dorsal annuli with spiny microtubercles (opisthosomal dorsal annuli smooth in 
Rhyncaphytoptus guanegounis
), tarsal empodium (em) 8-rayed (6-rayed in 
Rhyncaphytoptus guanegounis
).
